
	**Item #**: SCP-9947
**Object Class**: Euclid
**Special Containment Procedures**: Due to its anomalous properties, SCP-9947 cannot be relocated to a standard secure containment site; all security measures must be implemented on-site.

Under no circumstances are security or research personnel permitted to interact directly with SCP-9947. Only D-Class personnel are authorized for interaction, and strictly for approved research purposes only.

All research and observation of SCP-9947 must be conducted remotely from the dedicated observation laboratory. Any personnel attempting to leave the remote observation lab, or to interact with SCP-9947 without prior Level 4 authorization, must be immediately detained; termination is authorized if resistance occurs.

In the event of a containment breach, or if SCP-9947’s "blade" activates spontaneously for unknown reasons, full site evacuation is to be initiated immediately.
**Description**: SCP-9947 is an inoperative Japanese katana, previously owned by the notable historical figure █████████ during the 19th century. SCP-9947 has been abandoned and unmaintained since 19██. It remains unknown whether its anomalous properties manifested prior to or following its abandonment.

SCP-9947 is located in the central area of █████████, ██████████. It was first discovered when a group of teenage trespassers broke into the abandoned compound. All victims who entered within 15 meters of SCP-9947 were found deceased by local authorities after being reported missing.

Local police chief ███████ encountered SCP-9947 at a distance of 0.2 meters—a range that would result in instantaneous death. He immediately contacted Foundation assets to mobilize and contain SCP-9947.

Upon direct interaction with SCP-9947, subjects are instantly pulled into a complete "black-and-white dream state" (designated SCP-9947-1), per brain-computer interface data recovered from the latest surviving test subject. During this event, victims remain motionless and unresponsive in physical space as observed by on-site researchers.

Dream Insight (DI): A proprietary technology developed by current lead researcher Dr. J for SCP-9947.

Any subject entering SCP-9947-1 is addressed by a disembodied, anonymous announcer. The announcer can perceive and comprehend verbal communication from subjects within SCP-9947-1, but is not visible to any subject.

Current data indicates the announcer speaks exclusively in modern Japanese, yet understands most major modern languages including Chinese, English, French, German, and Russian. Its speech is fully comprehensible to subjects with no prior knowledge of Japanese.

The announcer will pose a single question regarding the subject’s deepest, true fear. All recorded responses to date have been classified as incorrect.

Following an "incorrect answer", the announcer enters a state of extreme rage, at which point all DI signals are permanently lost.

Approximately 2 seconds (real time) after initial contact, subjects begin to undergo rapid physical corrosion. This process is designated SCP-9947-2 and is currently irreversible.

Current research confirms: if a subject is physically pulled away from SCP-9947 before SCP-9947-2 initiates, instantaneous death can be prevented, and the onset of SCP-9947-2 can be halted.
The full historical origin and background of SCP-9947 remain under investigation.

**Addendum 1**: To date, no D-Class personnel who have entered SCP-9947’s "lethal radius" have returned alive. [DATA EXPUNGED]
— Dr. J
**Addendum 2**: Positive update: The latest SCP-9947 experiment has been successfully completed. Dr. J’s hypothesis has been verified. Most critically, we have secured a surviving test subject.D-4432 survived after providing an "incorrect answer" to the announcer, confirming the emergency extraction procedure is effective.
No subject has yet provided a response classified as "correct" within SCP-9947-1.

**All new findings will be appended to this document immediately.**
